      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:23:13",
      "text": [
        " إِذَا قَهْقَهْتَ فَقُلْ حِينَ تَفْرُغُ اللَّهُمَّ لَا تَمْقُتْنِي ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Abdullah Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al hakam, from Aban Bin Usman, from Khalid Bin Tahmaan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When you guffaw (loud bursts of laughter), so say when you are free (from it), ‘O Allah<sup>azwj</sup>! Do not Detest me’’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "13. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Aban ibn ‘Uthman from Khalid ibn Tahman from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “If you have laughed loudly, say, ‘O Lord, please, do not hate me.’” "
        ]
      }
